SIMPLE: petticoat
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petticoat
<hw>Pet"ti*coat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<ety>[<ets>Petty</ets> + <ets>coat</ets>.]</ety> <def>A loose
under-garment worn by women, and covering the body below the
waist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Petticoat government</b></col>, <cd>government by women,
whether in politics or domestic affairs.</cd> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> --
<col><b>Petticoat pipe</b></col> <fld>(Locomotives)</fld>, <cd>a short,
flaring pipe surrounding the blast nozzle in the smoke box, to equalize
the draft.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>petticoated</ent>⟦br⟧
